    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Introducing Repeat\r\nThis level has a new block - <code style=\"background-color: rgb(242, 24, 162); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">repeat</code>! You can use it to repeat code a certain number of times.\r\n\r\nLet's try to simplify our existing code with this new block instead!\r\n\r\n1) Drag the <code style=\"background-color: rgb(242, 24, 162); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">repeat</code> block over to the when run block. When you connect  it, the existing blocks will disappear! [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:repeat_workspace---id:when-run-block)\r\n2) Drag the <code style=\"background-color: rgb(116, 53, 178); color: white; border: none; box-shadow: inset -1px -1px 1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.5), inset 1px 1px 1px 0 rgb(255 255 255 / 0.8); padding: 4px\">play</code> block so it repeats 3 times [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:play_workspace---id-up-inside:repeat_workspace)\r\n\r\nWhen you're done, your song should sound exactly the same as the starter code - just with less blocks!\r\n\r\n> If you're stuck, try clicking the <i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i> icons for hints!\r\n",
